# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Conversational Agent (floating "Ask Agent" panel)
#
# When both values are set, the "Ask Agent" buttons in the Header and the
# LoanDetail header open a streaming chat panel wired to your UiPath agent.
# When either is empty, the panel still opens but shows a friendly setup
# message instead of crashing — so it's safe to ship unset.
#
# Required OAuth scopes on your External App (add to VITE_UIPATH_SCOPES too):
#   - OR.Jobs              (needed by conversations.create / startSession)
#   - ConversationalAgents (the streaming session itself)
#
# AGENT_ID:  NUMERIC ID of a Conversational Agent in UiPath (e.g. "1776514").
#            Find it in the Agents dashboard.
# FOLDER_ID: NUMERIC Orchestrator folder ID where the agent lives (e.g. "2596817").
#            NOT the folderKey GUID used elsewhere in this app. Look up via
#            Admin → Folders and find the numeric ID in the row details.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Folder key (GUID) for reference — not consumed by the SDK, which needs the
# numeric folderId below. Listed here so future maintainers can cross-check.
# VITE_CASE_MANAGER_FOLDER_KEY=f721de6e-a41f-4913-9d2c-184ffce88d32
VITE_CASE_MANAGER_AGENT_ID=2011015
VITE_CASE_MANAGER_FOLDER_ID=2911277
